  "response_text": "The commercial opens on the entrance to a modern public building with glass double doors and long, shiny vertical metal handles. A dark-sleeved arm comes in from the right and presses against the door area near the handle, suggesting someone is trying to get through without placing a bare hand directly on the handle. Through the glass, the inside of the building looks bright and airy, with large windows and soft daylight.\n\nA woman is then seen outside the entrance. She appears to be a young adult mother, with dark hair pulled back in a low ponytail, wearing a pale cardigan or sweater, blue jeans, dark shoes, and a burgundy shoulder bag. She is leaning awkwardly near the door, looking alert and a little wary. She raises one arm and shifts her body as if trying to manage the door while avoiding contact with the handle. Two young girls stand nearby behind her, both school-age children with backpacks; one has light blonde hair and a pink backpack, and the other has longer brown hair and a darker backpack. They wait close together at the doorway while the woman goes first.\n\nThe setting widens to show the glass-fronted building entrance, with multiple doors and reflective panels. The woman approaches the door while the girls remain just outside, watching her. She bends and angles her body toward the door, still seeming careful about what she touches. A man in a dark suit appears from inside and opens or holds the door as he steps out. The woman slips past him into the building, then turns back toward the children. She gestures to them with one hand, guiding them forward. The two girls walk toward the doorway and begin entering after her, while the woman stays near the open door, partly turned back to supervise them.\n\nThe scene changes to a bathroom sink area with small turquoise mosaic tiles on the wall. A bottle of Dial Complete sits beside the sink. The bottle has a white pump and a dark blue label with the large word “Dial” and the visible text “Complete” and “Foaming Hand Wash.” A hand presses down on the pump, and a thick mound of white foam dispenses into another hand held beneath it. The product is then shown standing clearly on the sink ledge near a chrome faucet and mirror, with a hand moving near the basin, ready to wash.",
